            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EThe%20exciting%20reality%20of%20Christianity%20is%20that%20a%20believer%20becomes%20a%20new%20person.%20In%20Ephesians%204%2C%20Paul%20contrasts%20the%20%22old%20man%22%20and%20the%20%22new%20man.%22%20The%20old%20man%20is%20a%20liar%2C%20while%20the%20new%20man%20tells%20the%20truth%20(Ephesians%204%3A25).%20The%20old%20man%20is%20always%20angry%2C%20but%20the%20new%20man%20controls%20anger%20and%20makes%20amends%20for%20it%20before%20the%20day%20is%20over%20(v.%2026).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThere%20are%20further%20contrasts%20between%20the%20old%20man%20and%20the%20new.%20The%20old%20man%20is%20stingy%20and%20steals%2C%20but%20the%20new%20man%20has%20a%20desire%20to%20work%20hard%20and%20give%20to%20others%20(v.%2028).%20The%20old%20man%20uses%20abusive%20language%2C%20but%20the%20new%20man%20speaks%20words%20that%20encourage%20others%20(v.%2029).%20The%20old%20man%20holds%20grudges%20and%20bitterness%20for%20years%2C%20but%20the%20new%20man%20is%20kind%2C%20tenderhearted%2C%20and%20forgiving%20(v.%2032).%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFor%20you%20to%20say%20that%20you%20have%20become%20a%20Christian%20yet%20continue%20to%20lie%2C%20vent%20your%20wrath%2C%20steal%2C%20curse%2C%20and%20harbor%20unforgiveness%20is%20a%20contradiction%20in%20terms.%20As%20a%20Christian%2C%20you%20must%20put%20off%20your%20old%20self%20and%20put%20on%20the%20new%20self%2C%20which%20was%20created%20to%20be%20like%20God.%20In%20this%20way%2C%20you%20will%20live%20a%20life%20%22worthy%20of%20your%20calling%22%20(v.%201)%20by%20the%20grace%20God%20has%20given%20you%20through%20salvation.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ERemember%3A%20You%20are%20a%20new%20person!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
